{"id": "EUVD-2025-22664", "enisaUuid": "cd28781d-b500-3c3f-9173-f13fc57c4fb9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nplatform/x86/amd: pmf: Use device managed allocations\n\nIf setting up smart PC fails for any reason then this can lead to\na double free when unloading amd-pmf.  This is because dev->buf was\nfreed but never set to NULL and is again freed in amd_pmf_remove().\n\nTo avoid subtle allocation bugs in failures leading to a double free\nchange all allocations into device managed allocations.", "datePublished": "2025-07-25T15:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:16", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0d10b532f861253c283863522d59d099fcb0796d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d9db3a941270d92bbd1a6a6b54a10324484f2f2d", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38421"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38421"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2d4b0fff-2b49-3460-b635-78e7b9fc8822", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3ed60e51ffdbfef14169bd967e21a6ba5e5ff42b"}, {"id": "4c00dadd-568a-36e0-b7c7-64678431cdaa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e70b4b8f93d7fcf8ee063a1d1f18782c4da3d335"}, {"id": "4c167bd8-c793-3f98-bf24-6e01cd2d33fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.14"}, {"id": "5f4e5b0d-2599-37a1-8c57-70328143b670", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.4"}, {"id": "63a12067-56f5-30df-828f-b35ae4c39b48", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "827e57b5-462c-30a0-aec6-2e2939623cbe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5b1122fc4995f308b21d7cfc64ef9880ac834d20 <d9db3a941270d92bbd1a6a6b54a10324484f2f2d"}, {"id": "85241e51-c66a-3061-a575-554b2e2ee91c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc3"}, {"id": "e931d202-5373-39cf-b28a-fda715e6177a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "ff011694-da45